%I A397771 #18 Jul 15 2026 22:24:24
%S A397771 0,0,7,32,190,1350,10765,92949,847511,8044399,78758786,790411028,
%T A397771 8095146289,84329102797
%N A397771 Number of homeomorphism classes of stable curves in the closure of the hyperelliptic locus of the moduli space of stable curves of genus g.
%C A397771 a(g) counts the combinatorial types of hyperelliptic stable curves of genus g over an algebraically closed field of characteristic != 2; equivalently, over C with the complex topology, this is the number of homeomorphism classes.
%C A397771 a(g) is also the number of stable hyperelliptic graphs of genus g (for the definition, see Kawaguchi and Yamaki).
%C A397771 a(g) is also the number of cluster pictures for 2g+2 points (for the definition, see Dokchitser et al.).
%H A397771 Tim Dokchitser, Vladimir Dokchitser, Céline Maistret, and Adam Morgan, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1704.08338">Semistable types of hyperelliptic curves</a>, arXiv:1704.08338 [math.NT], 2017; Algebraic curves and their applications, Contemp. Math. 724 (2019), 73-135. DOI: 10.1090/conm/724/14586.
%H A397771 Shu Kawaguchi and Kazuhiko Yamaki, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1304.6979">Rank of divisors on hyperelliptic curves and graphs under specialization</a>, arXiv:1304.6979 [math.AG], 2013-2014; Int. Math. Res. Notices, 12 (2015), 4121-4176. DOI: 10.1093/imrn/rnu059.
%H A397771 Max Schwegele, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.29016">Hyperelliptic Stable Curves</a>, arXiv:2606.29016 [math.AG], 2026.
%F A397771 a(g) = A007827(2*g + 2) for g >= 2.
%F A397771 a(g) <= A174224(g).
%e A397771 a(0) = a(1) = 0 because there are no stable curves of genus 0 or 1.
%e A397771 a(2) = A174224(2) = 7 because every stable curve of genus 2 is automatically hyperelliptic.
%Y A397771 Cf. A007827, A174224.
%K A397771 nonn,more,new
%O A397771 0,3
%A A397771 _Max Schwegele_, Jul 09 2026
